We are trying to associate a module with an EAR using the 
AddComponentToEnterpriseApplicationDataModelProvider. We are seeing the 
NullPointerException shown in comment #2. The problem was initially found in 
AST but, with some creativity, it can be reproduced in WTP with the use of the 
Generic WAS 6.0 runtime.

To reproduce do the following:

1. In a self-hosting environment, check out org.eclipse.jst.ws.axis.creation.ui 
(in jst/components/ws/plugins/)
2. Apply the attached patch to org.eclipse.jst.ws.axis.creation.ui/plugin.xml
3. Launch the runtime workbench
4. Go to Window > Preferences > Server > Installed Runtimes and add a Generic 
IBM WebSphere 6.0.x runtime
5. Create a Web project (J2EE 1.4, Generic WebSphere 6.0.x runtime target). Do 
not add the project to an EAR.
6. Select the Web project and launch the Web service wizard(File > New > Other 
> Web Services > Web Service
7.  Page 1: Select "Top Down Java bean Web service" as the Web service type.
8.  Page 2: Enter http://www.xmethods.net/sd/2001/TemperatureService.wsdl
9.  Page 3: Enter an EAR name in the Service EAR project field.
10. Page 4: Click Next. The error should occur.

Here is the code we are using to perform the association. Holler if we're doing 
something wrong.

	public static void associateComponentToEAR(IProject project, String 
componentName,IProject earProject, String earComponentName) {

IFlexibleProject flexearProj = ComponentCore.createFlexibleProject(earProject);
ComponentHandle earHandle = flexearProj.getComponent
(componentName).getComponentHandle();
IFlexibleProject flexcompProj = ComponentCore.createFlexibleProject(project);
ComponentHandle compHandle = flexcompProj.getComponent
(componentName).getComponentHandle();
IDataModel addComponentToEARDataModel = DataModelFactory.createDataModel(new 
AddComponentToEnterpriseApplicationDataModelProvider());
addComponentToEARDataModel.setProperty
(ICreateReferenceComponentsDataModelProperties.SOURCE_COMPONENT_HANDLE, 
earHandle);

List modList = (List) addComponentToEARDataModel.getProperty
(ICreateReferenceComponentsDataModelProperties.TARGET_COMPONENTS_HANDLE_LIST);
modList.add(compHandle);
addComponentToEARDataModel.setProperty
(ICreateReferenceComponentsDataModelProperties.TARGET_COMPONENTS_HANDLE_LIST, 
modList);
try {
  addComponentToEARDataModel.getDefaultOperation().execute(null, null);
} catch (ExecutionException e) {
  Logger.getLogger().log(e);
}

}
